# JSON parser
![Build Test](https://github.com/FloweyTheFlower420/JSON-parser/workflows/Build%20Test/badge.svg) 
This is a parser for JSON formated files.
## Build
First clone or download the repo
### Linux / Mac
To compile, make sure that `make` and `cmake` are installed. Then run
```
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make install
```
If you don't wish to install, run `make lib` instead of `make install`
This will generate the shared object file. If you wish to generate a static libary, run `make static`
## Examples
A basic example is:
```c++
#include "json/json.h"
#include <string>
#include <iostream>
using namespace json;
using namespace std;
int main()
{
  string json_buffer = "{\"Name\": \"Joe\"}";
  // parsing
  JSONparser parser;
  JSONobj obj; // stores value
  
  if(parser.deserialize(json_buffer, obj) != 0)
  {
    // error handling
    return -1;
  }
  std::cout << obj["Name"]; // get the value of 'Name' and print it
}
```
